  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Community based literacy, capacity and livelihoods development  (Somaliland)</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Unlike the rest of Somalia, Somaliland has enjoyed relative peace and stability for the last 13 years. However, poverty and illiteracy are still major problems.This project will target those who are most in danger of growing up without an education, and provide intensive lessons in Somali, Maths and English five times a week. It will work with the Ministry of Education to get as many children as possible back into school. It will also establish local community centres to help people help themselves. The centres will also teach those who have grown up without the chance to learn how to read and write. There will be a focus on making sure that women and girls are given opportunities to learn.</narrative>
  </description>
